On Escalation Ticket # 00412571 the new comment has been added: Marius Ghiurcau:

@Cristian-Alexandru Halmajan I think this should be handled by the Product team, we have some standard information that we provide to the customers in this case. Briefly the EPP client performs MITM in order to inspect the network traffic and yes, it might happen that some antivirus software detects this and there might be some incompatibilities between EPP and that AV (I know about a recent case with EPP and ESET, and issues when SSL filtering is enabled in ESET)

